d\na no-go theorem for the Lie bialgebras in 4 dimensions, which singles out the\nwell-known `$\\kappa$-deformation' as the only one that depends on the first\npower of the Planck length, or, alternatively, that possesses `manifest'\nspatial isotropy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Feb 2018 18:00:51 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 7 Mar 2018 18:02:26 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 21 Oct 2018 15:22:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-23"}
